    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="loc_jc.00382_large.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place">Camden<ptr target="loc.03861_n1"/></name>
                    <date when="1887-09-21">Sept: 21 2 P M</date>
                </dateline>
            </opener>
            <p>I suppose Herb<ptr target="n0262"/> must have sail'd from N Y this morning&#8212;he
                was here early yesterday &#38; took his picture &#38; I have seen or heard nothing
                of him since&#8212;Mrs Davis<ptr target="n6113"/> is sick, laid up, bad&#8212;A lady
                friend is here, helping us&#8212;I expect to be down Sunday by 12&#189;<ptr
                    target="loc.03861_n2"/>&#8212;Am sitting here by the window in the big chair
                &#38; have been all day&#8212;Weather rather pleasant.</p>
            <closer>
                <signed>Walt Whitman</signed>
            </closer>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001v" facs="loc_jc.00381_large.jpg" type="verso"/>
        </body>
